'''Talal Omar Abdillahi''' (born 12 May 1967) is a [[Djibouti]]an [[long-distance running|long-distance]] athlete.
Abdillahi has competed at the Olympics twice, firstly at the [[1988 Summer Olympics]], where he finished 18th in his heat in the [[Athletics at the 1988 Summer Olympics – Men's 10,000 metres|10,000 metres]] so didn't qualify for the final, four years later he entered the [[Athletics at the 1992 Summer Olympics – Men's marathon|marathon]] at the [[1992 Summer Olympics]] but he didn't finish the course.<ref>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ab/talal-omar-abdillahi-1.html Sports Reference Profile]</ref>
