{{Infobox stadium | name = Umm Salal Stadium | nickname = | logo_image = Umm Salal Stadium.jpg | logo_caption = Artist's impression of the new stadium | image = | caption = | fullname = | former_names = | location = [[Umm Salal]], [[Qatar]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = [[Grass]] | scoreboard = | construction_cost = | suites = | architect = [[Albert Speer, Jr.|Albert Speer & Partner GmbH]] | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 45,000 {{small|''(planned)''}} | record_attendance = | executive_suites = | dimensions = | acreage = | tenants = }} '''Umm Salal Stadium''' ({{Lang-ar|ملعب أم صلال}}) is a proposed [[association football|football]] stadium which will be built in [[Umm Salal]], [[Qatar]]. It is being designed by [[Albert Speer, Jr.|Albert Speer & Partner GmbH]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://archinect.com/news/article/150011093/with-the-middle-east-in-diplomatic-crisis-what-will-happen-to-qatar-s-building-projects|title=With the Middle East in diplomatic crisis, what will happen to Qatar's building projects?|publisher=Archinect News|author=Nicholas Korody|date=6 June 2017|accessdate=22 June 2018}}</ref>
==Plans== Umm Salal Stadium will be able to support 45,120 fans. The conceptual design of the stadium is based on traditional [[List of Egypt castles, forts, fortifications and city walls|Arabian forts]]. Post World Cup, the stadium will decrease its capacity to 25,500 seats and it will be used by [[Umm Salal Sport Club|Umm Salal F.C.]] as their [[home ground]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mic.qatarchamber.com/25|title=Key Projects Introduction|publisher=Qatar Chamber|accessdate=22 June 2018}}</ref>
